  keywords={behavioral economics, metatheory, complementarity, context-dependence},
  abstract = {This working paper introduces a metatheoretical framework for integrating diverse findings from behavioral economics. The Evidence-Based Framework (EBF) uses two core concepts: (1) context-dependence, captured through the context vector Psi, which modifies how behavioral parameters operate across situations; and (2) complementarity, captured through the gamma-matrix, which describes how different utility dimensions interact. The framework organizes 50+ years of behavioral research under a unified structure with 10 Core questions (10C), enabling systematic intervention design based on empirical evidence rather than ad-hoc assumptions.},
