  abstract = {Strategic decision making balances uniqueness and generality: managers must craft context-specific actions while abstracting from past cases to identify transferable patterns. We investigate via a laboratory NK task framed either abstractly (factors A, B, C) or contextually (Lemonade Stand). Pre-tests reveal that context improves immediate performance, but abstract framing benefits individuals with strong STEM skills and fosters higher learning rates over repeated rounds. Behavioral patterns show more early exploration in context and steeper explore-exploit shifts in abstraction.},
