  use_for = {LIT-O, METHOD-DESIGN, CORE-HOW},
  theory_support = {},
  evidence_tier = {1},
  parameter = {theory_dimensions: 6 (importance, interestingness, actionability, generality, simplicity, accuracy); commentaries_synthesized: 284; wordnet_themes: 14; trade_off_pairs: 9 negative covariation pairs; positive_covariation_pairs: 4},
  identification = {Systematic synthesis of 284 commentaries on theory; Wordnet linguistic validation (Wu-Palmer similarity); Python-based comparison of 63.4M possible configurations; 1000 random configuration test},
  external_validity = {All organizational and social science research; directly applicable to any field that builds and evaluates theory},
  session_ref = {},
  notes = {Metascience framework from Wharton (Andrew Carton) synthesizing 284 commentaries on what makes theory strong. Six dimensions: (1) IMPORTANCE - addresses significant problems; (2) INTERESTINGNESS - challenges assumptions, aha moments; (3) ACTIONABILITY - translates to practical levers (manipulate(X) in Dietz terms); (4) GENERALITY - explains broad phenomena; (5) SIMPLICITY - few constructs, clear logic; (6) ACCURACY - closely tethered to phenomena. Key insight: TRADE-OFFS are inevitable - impossible to optimize all six simultaneously (unicorn theories). First three dimensions = stages of consumption (input-process-output); last three = structure of logic. Theory hexagon shows 4 positive covariation links and 9 negative (trade-off) links. Six intellectual traditions drive conflicting expectations: applied scientists (actionability), disciplinary scholars (generality), empiricists (accuracy), humanists (importance), narrative scholars (interestingness), analytical modelers (simplicity). Recommendation: prioritize fewer dimensions per paper, all six across research program. Directly relevant to EBF: the EBF explicitly prioritizes ACTIONABILITY (manipulate(X) constructs like defaults, norms, incentives) and ACCURACY (context-specific parameters) while accepting trade-offs with GENERALITY. The Carton framework validates EBF design philosophy. Organization Science Vol 36 No 4. CC BY-NC-ND 4.0.},
}

